    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Type of glass negative where the glass plate is first coated with a mixture of albumin and potassium iodide. This is then dipped in a silver nitrate solution. Albumen glass negatives were not widely used and are difficult to visually distinguish from wet collodion glass negatives.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
